╭─ assistant [MainThread@3239804] ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ THOUGHT: The crash occurs due to incrementUnscheduledDeps asserting hasValidDependencies, but UnscheduledDeps can be set to InvalidDeps via resetUnscheduledDeps after                   │
│ clearDirectDependencies sets Dependencies=InvalidDeps. This leaves UnscheduledDeps in an inconsistent state, and later increment triggers the assertion. A safe fix is to make           │
│ resetUnscheduledDeps only set UnscheduledDeps when dependencies are valid; otherwise, set it to 0. This keeps the schedule data consistent and avoids meaningless increments.            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '1,20000s/void resetUnscheduledDeps() { UnscheduledDeps = Dependencies; }/void resetUnscheduledDeps() { UnscheduledDeps = hasValidDependencies() ? Dependencies : 0; }/'          │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && submit-patch                                                                                                                          │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
